FBIS4-31056 "dreeu107aa_94003" FBIS-EEU-94-107 Daily Report 3 Jun 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Akashi Says Serbs Resuming Withdrawal Akashi Says Serbs Resuming Withdrawal AU0306101494 Paris AFP in English 0952 GMT 3 Jun 94 AU0306101494 Paris AFP English BFN [Text] Geneva, June 3 (AFP) -- Serb forces resumed Friday their withdrawal from the UN-declared exclusion zone around Gorazde in eastern Bosnia, raising hopes that truce talks stalled since Thursday would be able to get under way, UN special envoy Yasushi Akashi said Friday. Speaking after a meeting with Bosnian Serb leader Radovan Karadzic, Akashi said he hoped the Geneva talks, aimed at securing an overall ceasefire in Bosnia-Herzegovina, could start on Saturday morning.
